																		It&#039;s OK to shoot them, they&#039;re just robots Morty!
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204569" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1459737567 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Apr 2016 02:39</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2485459">
									

<p>Been plugging away at this one since before the new year. Once the MTF contest and crackfic contests ended I found that I had some fresh ideas for this one, and ran with them.</p>
<p>Thanks to GreenWolf, minmin, and ribby97 for feedback and convincing me to go further and further with the concept. Also thanks to CumaeanSibyl and WrongJohnSilver for the grammar fixes and votes of confidence.</p>
<p>ALL BUT ONE OF THE CITED ARTICLES ARE FAKE.</p>
<p>The [May 1988] link is a real research paper written by Joanna Wallen from Sweden- in 2008. I pushed the date mentioned this article back by a couple decades to fit with the chronology of PL.<br />
As always, the scientists cited (with the exception of Ms. Wallen) are easter eggs of fictional chaps. Find them all and win nothing but my respect.</p>
<p>See more of my work on my <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/dr-arvind-desais-personnel-file">author page</a>!</p>

							</div>

								
