<blockquote>
<p>They really don't need to buy these fancy automatons</p>
</blockquote>
<p>But I argue that they could be useful. Given China's prosperity, there are more career options than soldiering in China. And China is a professional (i.e. non-conscript) army, despite their massive strength. Soldiers who will not mind dying for the sake of a mission or propaganda value would be a bonus to their cause.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>shrinking populations, making conscription of soldiers from citizens more problematic.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Agreeing with you on this, in general. Although it may be a grey area in Japan's case. Should we treat the ANA as weapons? If so, possession of the ANA by the JSDF might be slightly problematic.</p>

